Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Roughly crush the @hazelnuts{25%g} in the unopened #sachet{} using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat a #small frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the hazelnuts
and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Set aside.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}.

Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

When boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When there are ~{4%minutes} of cooking time left, add the broccoli and cook
for the remaining time.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium-high
heat. Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Cook the onion until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the garlic and @dried rosemary{1%sachet}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g},
@vegetable stock paste{10%g} and the @water{100%ml}(for the sauce).

Simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once thickened,
stir in the cooked pasta and broccoli.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @truffle zest{1%sachet}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water
if the sauce looks a little too thick.

Share your creamy truffle linguine between the #serving bowls{}.

Finish by sprinkling over the toasted hazelnuts.

Enjoy!